In a large #bowl{}, place @haloumi{2%packet} and cover with water to soak.

Thinly slice @red onion{1}.

In a small bowl, combine the @white wine vinegar{1/4%cup} and a good pinch of @sugar{pinch} and @salt{pinch}.

Scrunch sliced onion in your hands, then add it to pickling liquid. Add enough water to just cover onion. Set aside.

Thinly slice @kumato{1} into wedges.

Slice @avocado{1}(in half) and scoop out flesh and thinly slice.

Finely chop @garlic{1}.

Cut or tear @bake-at-home ciabatta{4%slices} into bite-sized chunks.

In a large #frying pan{}, heat a generous drizzle of @olive oil{1%drizzle} over medium-high heat.

Cook ciabatta until golden and slightly crispy, ~{5-6%minutes}. Season to taste.

In the last minute of cook time, add garlic, a pinch of @?chilli flakes{1%sachet} (if using) and another drizzle of olive oil, tossing, until fragrant. Transfer to a bowl.

Drain haloumi and pat dry. Cut the haloumi into 1cm-thick slices.

Return frying pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil.

Cook haloumi until golden brown, ~{1-2%minutes} each side. Cook in batches if your pan is getting crowded.

Remove pan from heat and add the @honey{1%tbs} and a splash of water, turning to coat.

Drain pickled onion.

In a large bowl, combine @basil pesto{1%packet} and a good drizzle of olive oil.

Add @spinach & rocket mix{1%packet}, kumato, avocado, pickled onion and croutons. Toss to combine and season to taste.

Divide rainbow Kumato salad between bowls. Top with seared haloumi.

Garnish with @pine nuts{1%packet}. Enjoy!